1
00:02:49,480 --> 00:02:53,360
It was in a country far away.
I don't know which one.

2
00:02:53,480 --> 00:02:55,390
But it was a distant land.

3
00:02:55,440 --> 00:02:57,360
A prince lost his mind
and imagined himself...

4
00:02:57,480 --> 00:03:01,600
- ... to be a rooster.
- A rooster? Like this one?

5
00:03:01,880 --> 00:03:05,760
Yes. He took refuge
under the dining-room table...

6
00:03:05,880 --> 00:03:10,600
...striped naked, and refused
to eat anything but grain.

7
00:03:10,720 --> 00:03:13,760
- And then?
- The King called in magicians and doctors...

8
00:03:13,880 --> 00:03:17,400
...to cure his son,
but to no avail.

9
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:22,160
One day, an unknown sage
arrived, took off his clothes...

10
00:03:22,280 --> 00:03:27,280
...and joined the prince under the table,
saying he too was a rooster.

11
00:03:27,560 --> 00:03:31,440
Eventually, the sage convinced
the prince to get dressed.

12
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:35,440
And finally to sit down and eat
with the others. "Don't ever think"...

13
00:03:35,560 --> 00:03:37,520
...said the sage, "... that by
eating like...

14
00:03:37,570 --> 00:03:39,440
...a man, with other
men at the table...

15
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:42,440
...a rooster ceases to
be what he is. "

16
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:44,760
"You can do anything with...

17
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:47,000
...men in their world.
Or even for them. "

18
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:49,240
"And yet remain the
rooster that your are. "

19
00:03:49,290 --> 00:03:51,400
I'm so proud of you, Benjamin.

20
00:03:51,480 --> 00:03:55,360
Such young little fellow, and
brighter than all the adults.

21
00:03:55,480 --> 00:03:58,360
Guess what?
I have some money.

22
00:03:58,680 --> 00:04:01,240
How would you like to
eat in a restaurant?

23
00:04:01,290 --> 00:04:03,800
A restaurant?
Really?

24
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:08,800
What do you think
about her and me, huh?

25
00:04:08,880 --> 00:04:11,520
- You'd be fine.
- Yeah, it's true!

26
00:04:11,880 --> 00:04:13,990
Miss? Miss!

27
00:04:14,040 --> 00:04:16,240
She has nice tits,
and a fine ass.

28
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:20,800
- I wouldn't say no to sleeping with her.
- Miss!

29
00:04:20,880 --> 00:04:22,720
Miss, miss!

30
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:27,800
Hey, miss! Where the hell are
the...

31
00:04:27,850 --> 00:04:30,440
...girls in this stinking
place, huh?

32
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:48,990
Could I have another one, please?

33
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:51,400
Hey, fatty!
You should watch your weight.

34
00:04:51,480 --> 00:04:55,360
Or soon you'll be wider than
you're tall. Like a potato.

35
00:04:55,480 --> 00:04:58,360
Like a stuffed pig!

36
00:04:58,680 --> 00:05:01,560
Hey, fatty!
What's your name?

37
00:05:02,080 --> 00:05:06,360
He's not fat!
He's my brother and he's strong.

38
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:11,280
I'm a blacksmith. My name
is Zishe. Zishe Breitbart.

39
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:18,840
Hey, fatty!
I'm talking to you.

40
00:05:19,560 --> 00:05:22,680
Our fatty is a jew.

41
00:05:22,800 --> 00:05:25,680
A big fat jew.

42
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:28,600
A fat one, and a thin one.

43
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:33,600
The fat jew eats too much,
and the thin jew not enough.

44
00:05:33,720 --> 00:05:36,470
Hey, fatty! Why doesn't...

45
00:05:36,520 --> 00:05:39,320
...the little one
eat anything, huh?

46
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:41,360
You should eat more,
like your fat brother.

47
00:05:41,410 --> 00:05:43,360
Good idea.

48
00:05:43,440 --> 00:05:46,400
You're too thin.

49
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:51,080
- The thick and the thin...
- ... together through thick and thin.

50
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:59,680
- Open your mouth!
- And eat!

51
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:14,080
Hey!

52
00:06:15,480 --> 00:06:17,440
Hey!

53
00:06:25,960 --> 00:06:28,220
You will pay me for this!
Have you an idea...

54
00:06:28,270 --> 00:06:30,480
...how much beer that was?
One hectolitre.

55
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:34,680
And do you know how much a barrel costs?
And how much that table costs?

56
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:36,960
It wasn't his fault,
the others started it!

57
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:39,160
As for the money,
I'd like to pay.

58
00:06:39,280 --> 00:06:43,160
Yes, we'd really like to pay for
this, but we don't have any money.

59
00:06:43,280 --> 00:06:45,470
What I should do
is call the police.

60
00:06:45,520 --> 00:06:47,800
But I think there's a way
for you to pay for the damage.

61
00:06:47,880 --> 00:06:51,760
The circus is in town.
Outside, by the gate.

62
00:06:51,880 --> 00:06:55,760
There's a famous "strongman".
And there's prize money to be won...

63
00:06:55,880 --> 00:06:57,920
...for the man who can beat him!

64
00:07:58,960 --> 00:08:03,560
Ladies and Gentlemen,
dear children!

65
00:08:03,640 --> 00:08:08,560
I would like to announce that our
Hercules has a challenger!

66
00:08:09,360 --> 00:08:12,080
A strong young man, without doubt.

67
00:08:12,130 --> 00:08:14,800
But in more than 20 years...

68
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:18,400
...our Hercules,
our Colossus of Rhodes...

69
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:22,400
...has never been defeated.

70
00:08:28,760 --> 00:08:32,360
For years we have been
raising the prize...

71
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:36,880
...to the amount of 5.000 Zloty
for any man...

72
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:42,600
...who proves himself stronger.
Not without reason...

73
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:47,160
...the ancients have proclaimed
the Colossus of Rhodes...

74
00:08:47,280 --> 00:08:51,640
...one of the 7
Wonders of the World!

75
00:09:13,280 --> 00:09:16,160
And now, highly esteemed audience...

76
00:09:16,210 --> 00:09:19,040
...his challenger this evening:

77
00:09:19,680 --> 00:09:23,360
Zishe Breitbart!
Blacksmith from this town.

78
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:25,320
I can do more!
I can do more!

79
00:12:00,880 --> 00:12:04,760
Yitzak, come! There's a visitor.
A real gentleman.

80
00:12:04,880 --> 00:12:08,840
- What does he want?
- I don't know. He arrived in a motorcar.

81
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:13,680
And, oh my God, I have
nothing to offer him.

82
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:29,160
Landwehr. Alfred Landwehr.

83
00:12:29,280 --> 00:12:32,160
Pleased to meet you,
Mr. Breitbart.

84
00:12:32,210 --> 00:12:35,040
And this is your strong son.

85
00:12:37,040 --> 00:12:40,000
- Please! Sit down!
- Thank you.

86
00:12:46,320 --> 00:12:48,720
I'm an agent for variety artists.

87
00:12:48,760 --> 00:12:51,160
Dancers, chucklers, magicians.

88
00:12:51,280 --> 00:12:55,960
Everything that is in demand.
And the demand in Berlin is enormous.

89
00:12:56,040 --> 00:12:59,000
I possess an instinct for
great talents.

90
00:12:59,050 --> 00:13:01,960
For people who will go
straight to the top.

91
00:13:02,080 --> 00:13:05,960
I was at the circus yesterday to
see the local strongman, when your son-

92
00:13:06,080 --> 00:13:08,040
You need not go on.
We are respectable people.

93
00:13:08,090 --> 00:13:09,960
For a jew this is not
the right thing.

94
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:13,840
But the most gifted people
in cinema, in theatre and art are.

95
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:18,400
I never even thought about leaving.
I belong in this smithy...

96
00:13:18,480 --> 00:13:23,000
- ... in our little Shtetl.
- You see, our jewish Shtetls...

97
00:13:23,080 --> 00:13:25,070
...are like holy
books, open...

98
00:13:25,120 --> 00:13:28,200
...to the eyes of God. And the
Day of the Torment...

99
00:13:28,280 --> 00:13:31,240
...even the fish tremble
in the brook.

100
00:13:31,360 --> 00:13:36,160
In spring, during Passover,
the trees rejoice.

101
00:13:36,480 --> 00:13:40,360
Sir... you're like a shopkeeper,
with empty shelves.

102
00:13:40,480 --> 00:13:42,680
With nothing to sell.

103
00:13:45,880 --> 00:13:49,320
Son... you'll have
to attend university!

104
00:13:51,120 --> 00:13:52,680
You've said that beautifully...

105
00:13:52,730 --> 00:13:54,240
...really.

106
00:13:54,640 --> 00:13:57,600
Do you know how old the
boy is? 9!

107
00:13:58,960 --> 00:14:01,790
This little fellow
is just 9 years old.

108
00:14:01,840 --> 00:14:04,720
And to think that this
is my brother, Benjamin.

109
00:14:05,480 --> 00:14:08,520
Look at what an incredible
boy my brother is.

110
00:14:15,960 --> 00:14:19,840
Good morning, ladies and gentlemen.
Are you all right?

111
00:14:19,960 --> 00:14:22,920
- Yes, thank you.
- Fine! Me too.

112
00:14:27,720 --> 00:14:31,760
Good morning, Mr. Landwehr!
We've just been talking about you.

113
00:14:31,880 --> 00:14:34,390
Did you sleep in the motorcar?

114
00:14:34,440 --> 00:14:37,000
There isn't even a hotel
around here to spend the night.

115
00:14:37,120 --> 00:14:41,880
- Good morning. Mornin'. Mornin'.
- You are an exceptional man.

116
00:14:42,280 --> 00:14:44,480
I am, when i'm after
an exceptional talent.

117
00:14:44,530 --> 00:14:46,720
Zishe, listen!

118
00:14:46,800 --> 00:14:49,520
I want you to come with
me just for the day!

119
00:14:49,570 --> 00:14:51,560
I have something to show you.

120
00:14:52,360 --> 00:14:56,480
- But i can't leave. I must work.
- Your father...

121
00:14:56,560 --> 00:14:58,500
...would excuse you
for an afternoon, huh?

122
00:14:58,550 --> 00:15:00,440
My son is able to make up his
own mind...

123
00:15:00,490 --> 00:15:01,990
...about such things.

124
00:15:02,040 --> 00:15:04,520
You'll be most interested to see
what i'm going to show you.

125
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:42,110
Look Zishe, look
at all the motorcars!

126
00:15:42,160 --> 00:15:45,120
There must be every motorcar
in the whole world...

127
00:15:45,480 --> 00:15:47,270
...right in Berlin!

128
00:15:47,320 --> 00:15:49,160
More than motorcars, young man.
Watch what's coming.

129
00:15:54,120 --> 00:15:57,000
That's a flying machine!
I've read about it.

130
00:16:02,480 --> 00:16:05,840
Look at how many
people it can carry.

131
00:16:06,800 --> 00:16:10,680
Aeroplanes will never compete
against that.

132
00:16:33,560 --> 00:16:35,520
Benjamin!

133
00:16:36,960 --> 00:16:39,920
- Benjamin, wake up!
- I am awake!

134
00:16:41,480 --> 00:16:44,520
- I've been thinking.
- So have I.

135
00:16:49,680 --> 00:16:52,520
Do you believe God gives to
each of us a gift?

136
00:16:52,570 --> 00:16:55,360
Of course.

137
00:16:55,680 --> 00:16:58,400
God made me strong,
Benjamin. Don't you think...

138
00:16:58,450 --> 00:17:01,120
...that he made me strong
for a reason?

139
00:17:01,200 --> 00:17:06,000
A blacksmith needs to be strong.

140
00:17:06,120 --> 00:17:10,880
But I am stronger than a
blacksmith needs to be.

141
00:17:11,360 --> 00:17:16,040
Sometimes we don't understand
why God does what He does.

142
00:17:19,880 --> 00:17:22,920
This is what I must find out.

143
00:17:26,680 --> 00:17:29,320
- Zishe?
- What? Tell me.

144
00:17:31,280 --> 00:17:35,160
The Book of Prophets says:
"Spare me...

145
00:17:35,280 --> 00:17:39,160
...that i may recover strength,
before i go hence...

146
00:17:40,120 --> 00:17:43,320
...and be no more.
And be no more. "

147
00:17:59,960 --> 00:18:01,920
- And?
- And, what?

148
00:18:02,480 --> 00:18:05,360
- What do you think about it?
- About what?

149
00:18:05,480 --> 00:18:07,350
Berlin.

150
00:18:07,400 --> 00:18:09,360
Let me talk to the
Rabbi first.

151
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:13,760
But before anything, we have to
celebrate Passover.

152
00:18:13,880 --> 00:18:15,240
But...

153
00:18:18,400 --> 00:18:20,640
Children, when we fled Egypt,
we didn't...

154
00:18:20,690 --> 00:18:22,840
...have time for the
bread to rise.

155
00:18:22,960 --> 00:18:26,840
Hannah? What happened
when we came to the sea?

156
00:18:26,960 --> 00:18:30,320
- Hashem opened the seas.
- Yes, he did!

157
00:18:31,800 --> 00:18:34,240
And, Raffael? How many
years did we stay in the desert?

158
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:35,720
Forty.

159
00:18:35,800 --> 00:18:38,760
Yes. All right.

160
00:18:39,200 --> 00:18:42,240
- Search for it!
- Yes!

161
00:18:55,120 --> 00:18:57,080
Where is it?

162
00:19:03,480 --> 00:19:06,360
It must be somewhere.

163
00:19:09,080 --> 00:19:12,600
Maybe under the pillow.
Hannele found it!

164
00:19:12,720 --> 00:19:15,600
- Wonderful!
- Hannele found it!

165
00:19:15,720 --> 00:19:19,160
- She has found it.
- Very well!

166
00:19:19,280 --> 00:19:21,240
Wonderful!

167
00:19:22,480 --> 00:19:25,360
- How much do you want for it?
- 6 Zloty.

168
00:19:27,040 --> 00:19:30,000
No, that's too much!

169
00:19:30,080 --> 00:19:31,790
Yes...

170
00:19:31,840 --> 00:19:33,600
- 6!
- Yes.

171
00:19:33,880 --> 00:19:38,400
I want to thank the Allmighty
for my good wife, and my children.

172
00:19:38,480 --> 00:19:43,080
You are the salt of earth.
And you fill my heart with joy.

173
00:19:44,280 --> 00:19:47,360
Today, I want to thank
God in particular...

174
00:19:47,410 --> 00:19:50,440
...for my strong firstborn.

175
00:19:50,960 --> 00:19:55,080
Zishe, my son! You will
go out into the World...

176
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:58,360
...but don't ever forget
who you are!

177
00:21:06,960 --> 00:21:09,920
Hold on! Hold on!

178
00:21:37,080 --> 00:21:41,200
I've travelled very far. I've been as
far as Vilna. But a thing like this...

179
00:21:41,280 --> 00:21:43,240
...a thing like this i've
never seen before.

180
00:21:43,290 --> 00:21:45,160
Can you give me a ride?

181
00:21:45,280 --> 00:21:50,000
- Where can we take you?
- You're not going to Berlin, by any chance?

182
00:21:59,480 --> 00:22:02,360
- Are you hungry?
- All the time.

183
00:22:02,480 --> 00:22:05,360
My mother has never been
able to feed me enough.

184
00:22:05,480 --> 00:22:09,680
And you want to walk
all the way to Berlin?

185
00:22:10,480 --> 00:22:15,000
Yes. I have a ticket for
the train, first class.

186
00:22:15,120 --> 00:22:20,080
But i'm going to return the ticket, and
my mother will get a new dress instead.

187
00:22:20,280 --> 00:22:24,160
I've heard there are
many pretty girls in Berlin.

188
00:22:24,280 --> 00:22:28,640
Girls like you won't find in
the country. Maybe you'll meet one.

189
00:22:28,720 --> 00:22:32,240
I have already, sort of.
In a dream.

190
00:22:33,640 --> 00:22:37,520
But I couldn't see her face, because...
I know it sounds strange...

191
00:22:37,640 --> 00:22:42,560
...but there was so much light.
I think she was a princess.

192
00:23:16,560 --> 00:23:20,440
You didn't come specially for me?
How did you know?

193
00:23:20,560 --> 00:23:23,120
Your reputation is
faster than your feet.

194
00:23:23,170 --> 00:23:25,680
My name is Delilah.

195
00:23:26,480 --> 00:23:29,440
Better take care, Samson!

196
00:23:54,800 --> 00:23:58,680
Berlin, May 1932

197
00:24:58,280 --> 00:25:01,400
It's me, Zishe!
Zishe Breitbart!

198
00:25:03,040 --> 00:25:06,480
You want to talk to Mr. Landwehr?

199
00:25:06,600 --> 00:25:10,160
Are you still there?
Hello? Hello?

200
00:25:10,480 --> 00:25:14,240
- Speak please.
- What?

201
00:25:15,480 --> 00:25:18,360
- Please speak.
- Yes!

202
00:25:18,480 --> 00:25:21,360
- Where are you?
- In Berlin.

203
00:25:21,480 --> 00:25:23,430
Come and see us at once.
Mr. Landwehr...

204
00:25:23,480 --> 00:25:26,480
...is expecting you. We
thought you were lost.

205
00:25:32,080 --> 00:25:34,280
A girl you say.

206
00:25:34,480 --> 00:25:36,440
And she wanted to marry
you at once?

207
00:25:36,490 --> 00:25:38,360
Well, actually no.

208
00:25:38,480 --> 00:25:40,550
She just wanted to keep me.

209
00:25:40,600 --> 00:25:42,760
Don't just stand there,
have a seat.

210
00:25:42,840 --> 00:25:44,800
Thank you.

211
00:25:48,680 --> 00:25:53,200
You realize, that the possibilities
to employ you are...

212
00:25:53,280 --> 00:25:56,880
- ... somewhat limited.
- Yes? What do you mean by that?

213
00:25:57,960 --> 00:26:01,240
No, no, don't be afraid!

214
00:26:02,280 --> 00:26:07,240
I'm good at the work i do.
The best, if i may say so.

215
00:26:08,800 --> 00:26:13,160
I'm going to employ you in an
establishment called...

216
00:26:13,280 --> 00:26:16,240
..."Hanussen's Palace
of the Occult".

217
00:26:17,480 --> 00:26:21,360
I don't quite understand.
What am i supposed to do there?

218
00:26:21,480 --> 00:26:25,760
I've talked to Hanussen, and he
was immediately pleased with my idea.

219
00:26:25,880 --> 00:26:29,760
Hanussen has understood something
about the insecurity of our times.

220
00:26:29,880 --> 00:26:32,120
Inflation, unemployment,
mass strikes...

221
00:26:32,170 --> 00:26:34,400
...attempted coups, bank rushes.

222
00:26:34,480 --> 00:26:38,360
People long for a
strong man, a leader.

223
00:26:38,480 --> 00:26:42,360
And Hanussen is the clairvoyant,
the prophet of this longing.

224
00:26:42,480 --> 00:26:45,360
And what does that have
to do with me?

225
00:26:46,200 --> 00:26:51,120
I can tell you! You will be
a kind of contrasting program:

226
00:26:51,800 --> 00:26:54,440
The strenght of the body,
against the...

227
00:26:54,490 --> 00:26:57,080
...dark powers of the
spirit of the occult.

228
00:26:57,200 --> 00:27:00,280
And i have to point out to you
right now that you...

229
00:27:00,330 --> 00:27:02,720
...must play a certain game.

230
00:27:02,840 --> 00:27:06,120
I can't do that.
I'm strong, that's all.

231
00:27:06,200 --> 00:27:11,160
I don't demand anything else from you.
And furthermore, you'll keep your mouth shut!

232
00:27:11,640 --> 00:27:14,440
I'll meet with tomorrow
at Hanussen's.

233
00:27:15,880 --> 00:27:18,000
Dismissed!

234
00:27:18,320 --> 00:27:23,320
PALACE OF THE OCCULT

235
00:27:29,360 --> 00:27:31,320
No, impossible!

236
00:27:32,040 --> 00:27:34,920
What if he carries a weapon,
pearhaps a spear?

237
00:27:35,040 --> 00:27:38,920
No, he shouldn't look like
some primitive man.

238
00:27:39,040 --> 00:27:41,960
Someone from primordial times.

239
00:27:42,010 --> 00:27:44,880
That's my demand.
Take it off!

240
00:27:44,960 --> 00:27:48,920
Take it off! I hope you're all
