very very much.

985
01:40:29,280 --> 01:40:32,280
But i know you must go.

986
01:40:48,680 --> 01:40:52,600
Zishe, dear, please be careful,
you're breaking me in two.

987
01:40:52,680 --> 01:40:56,600
I'm a woman, you must
be very tender.

988
01:41:04,760 --> 01:41:08,760
I don't think you know why
i asked you to wear this dress.

989
01:41:08,880 --> 01:41:10,120
There is--

990
01:41:10,640 --> 01:41:12,480
I have something for you.

991
01:41:29,560 --> 01:41:33,480
- You didn't... did you?
- Yes, yes i did.

992
01:41:43,480 --> 01:41:46,240
Beethoven's Third Piano Concerto.
Second Movement.

993
01:41:46,640 --> 01:41:48,200
But, in Heaven's name...

994
01:41:48,200 --> 01:41:50,200
...we've never
rehearsed together.

995
01:41:50,200 --> 01:41:52,200
Don't worry madame,
the important thing is...

996
01:41:52,200 --> 01:41:56,200
...that we have rehearsed.
We shall follow you.

997
01:45:21,280 --> 01:45:24,280
CANCELLED

998
01:45:25,880 --> 01:45:27,800
CANCELLED DUE TO ILLNESS

999
01:45:59,160 --> 01:46:01,240
Zishe Breitbart? Unmistakable.

1000
01:46:01,240 --> 01:46:03,280
Thank you for being
at our disposal.

1001
01:46:03,400 --> 01:46:07,280
- I want to see it for myself.
- Get in!

1002
01:46:09,680 --> 01:46:11,880
Prepare yourself, it won't
be a pleasant sight.

1003
01:46:24,880 --> 01:46:28,120
Due identification was made
very difficult by the fact...

1004
01:46:28,120 --> 01:46:30,360
- Can you take this?
- Yes.

1005
01:46:30,480 --> 01:46:33,320
By the fact that the corpse
shows at least 20 bullet...

1006
01:46:33,320 --> 01:46:36,200
...holes and has been
disfigured by wild animals.

1007
01:46:36,280 --> 01:46:40,200
In other words:
wild bears have eaten the face...

1008
01:46:40,280 --> 01:46:43,160
...and half of the body.

1009
01:47:40,200 --> 01:47:43,160
I know this man.

1010
01:47:52,280 --> 01:47:57,280
Western Poland, December 1932

1011
01:48:51,960 --> 01:48:53,880
Zishe... Zishe!

1012
01:48:55,560 --> 01:48:57,880
It is Zishe!

1013
01:49:01,680 --> 01:49:06,680
- Welcome! Welcome!
- Zishe!

1014
01:49:07,000 --> 01:49:10,280
Zishe, you've become
a famous man!

1015
01:49:12,200 --> 01:49:15,960
- Your brother will be so pleased.
- Who? Benjamin?

1016
01:49:16,200 --> 01:49:20,760
- Yes. Didn't your mother ever write to you?
- Yes. Is Benjamin ill?

1017
01:49:20,800 --> 01:49:24,880
No. But don't you know that
every day since you gone away...

1018
01:49:25,000 --> 01:49:27,440
...he's been sitting on
the steps of your house...

1019
01:49:27,440 --> 01:49:28,880
Every day.

1020
01:49:29,000 --> 01:49:31,480
...looking in the
direction you went?

1021
01:49:31,480 --> 01:49:32,760
For hours.

1022
01:49:36,360 --> 01:49:38,880
I have to see him.

1023
01:50:01,560 --> 01:50:04,480
Zishe, my son!

1024
01:50:54,080 --> 01:50:56,880
Come closer!
Come closer!

1025
01:50:57,960 --> 01:51:00,880
- Come here! Come closer, please!
- Please.

1026
01:51:01,560 --> 01:51:04,480
Come closer! Come here!

1027
01:51:04,680 --> 01:51:06,880
Come closer!

1028
01:51:07,960 --> 01:51:12,200
We have to get strong.
We shall need a thousand Samsons.

1029
01:51:12,280 --> 01:51:16,200
We must be strong.
We... we have to defend.

1030
01:51:16,280 --> 01:51:19,400
What i mean to say is...
I mean...

1031
01:51:19,400 --> 01:51:23,480
I shall need thousands of strong
young men, to protect and defend...

1032
01:51:23,560 --> 01:51:25,080
...our people.

1033
01:51:25,080 --> 01:51:27,800
I foresee something terrible
happening to our people.

1034
01:51:27,960 --> 01:51:31,680
Something horrific.
The Nazis in Germany...

1035
01:51:31,800 --> 01:51:35,680
Because we need thousands of Samsons.
I will show you how to get strong.

1036
01:51:35,800 --> 01:51:37,840
All right, Zishe!
You know we admire you.

1037
01:51:37,840 --> 01:51:39,680
We are proud of you.

1038
01:51:39,800 --> 01:51:41,720
But how, i ask,
could the Nazis...

1039
01:51:41,720 --> 01:51:43,680
...pose any threat to us?

1040
01:51:43,800 --> 01:51:46,200
The Nazis, yes the
Nazis in Germany!

1041
01:51:46,200 --> 01:51:48,600
Germany is no
danger for Poland.

1042
01:51:48,600 --> 01:51:50,600
Since they've lost the
Great War they are not...

1043
01:51:50,600 --> 01:51:52,600
...even allowed to
have an army anymore.

1044
01:51:52,600 --> 01:51:54,880
That is not quite true.
They are allowed...

1045
01:51:54,880 --> 01:51:57,160
...100.000 men.
No heavy arms...

1046
01:51:57,280 --> 01:51:59,320
...no aeroplanes,
no battle ships.

1047
01:51:59,320 --> 01:52:02,360
Yes, but professor, Poland's borders are secure, are they not?

1048
01:52:02,480 --> 01:52:07,280
I think so, yes. If there's a
danger, it'll come from Russia.

1049
01:52:07,400 --> 01:52:10,280
Listen, listen to me!
I see it! I see it!

1050
01:52:10,280 --> 01:52:11,800
What is it?

1051
01:52:12,280 --> 01:52:15,800
The horror! It's... it's...

1052
01:52:18,760 --> 01:52:23,560
The horror! It's real.

1053
01:52:26,280 --> 01:52:29,280
Please stay!
You must listen to me!

1054
01:52:58,080 --> 01:53:02,360
- Benjamin's missing. Where is he?
- He's in the workshop.

1055
01:53:02,680 --> 01:53:06,880
- He stays in the workshop.
- I'm going to get him.

1056
01:53:27,160 --> 01:53:30,360
I'm not coming.
I've to get strong.

1057
01:53:30,400 --> 01:53:33,000
Even if nobody
else believes you.

1058
01:53:35,160 --> 01:53:39,880
If you want to get strong,
you have to eat properly too.

1059
01:53:43,560 --> 01:53:46,760
There's no muscle there.

1060
01:53:50,080 --> 01:53:54,280
It's better for you to study.
Study at studies.

1061
01:54:16,680 --> 01:54:21,000
I am the new Samson!
I want to be your protector.

1062
01:54:21,400 --> 01:54:23,520
But i can't do this alone.

1063
01:54:23,520 --> 01:54:26,280
You have to become strong,
like me! All of you.

1064
01:54:26,360 --> 01:54:30,280
And i'm a woodcutter. I can
handle an axe. But are you really..

1065
01:54:30,360 --> 01:54:32,600
...so strong? If you want
to tell us something...

1066
01:54:32,600 --> 01:54:34,760
...you have to show
us something first.

1067
01:54:34,880 --> 01:54:37,800
Did you never hear about
Zishe, the Aryan King?

1068
01:54:37,800 --> 01:54:39,280
The new Samson.

1069
01:54:39,400 --> 01:54:43,880
- That's what he called himself in Berlin.
- But we want to see something.

1070
01:54:43,960 --> 01:54:47,960
Some real good stuff.
You know, strong.

1071
01:55:12,200 --> 01:55:15,080
Impressive! But these are polish nails, probably greased.

1072
01:55:19,000 --> 01:55:21,120
I bet you can't do
it with this one.

1073
01:55:21,120 --> 01:55:22,880
Of course he can.

1074
01:55:23,000 --> 01:55:25,160
He can do much more.

1075
01:55:36,200 --> 01:55:39,400
Look at this! It went
all the way through.

1076
01:55:39,800 --> 01:55:43,800
It doesn't look too deep,
but it could get infected.

1077
01:55:44,080 --> 01:55:46,880
The village barber
can stitch it up.

1078
01:55:47,680 --> 01:55:49,680
Vodka!

1079
01:55:51,480 --> 01:55:55,400
- We'll put some vodka on it.
- Ridiculous!

1080
01:55:55,480 --> 01:55:59,480
- The thing was rusty.
- Vodka, we'll drink the vodka!

1081
01:55:59,680 --> 01:56:02,760
And then we'll go on talking.

1082
01:56:04,880 --> 01:56:06,880
Cheers!

1083
01:56:07,000 --> 01:56:09,000
Yes!

1084
01:57:01,080 --> 01:57:03,880
You should let the doctor
look at that.

1085
01:57:29,000 --> 01:57:31,960
Under the table.
The prince.

1086
01:57:35,000 --> 01:57:38,760
- There's a rooster!
- Zishe, you have a fever.

1087
01:57:39,480 --> 01:57:42,360
There's no rooster.

1088
01:57:56,280 --> 01:57:58,280
JEWISH HOSPITAL

1089
01:58:33,280 --> 01:58:36,360
Mr. Breitbart?
Mr. Breitbart?

1090
01:58:38,200 --> 01:58:42,280
Can you hear me?
Zishe, can you hear me?

1091
01:58:45,960 --> 01:58:50,680
We have to operate at once.
And we'll have to amputate the leg.

1092
01:58:51,560 --> 01:58:54,600
It's the only way to
save his life.

1093
01:58:54,600 --> 01:58:58,280
I'm sorry, but we
have no choice.

1094
01:59:10,760 --> 01:59:13,800
- Will it grow again?
- Yes, of course!

1095
01:59:14,280 --> 01:59:19,160
- It'll take only one or two months.
- Hannele, come down from the bed.

1096
01:59:19,200 --> 01:59:22,600
Why don't you let her stay? It
makes me happy when she's with me.

1097
01:59:25,880 --> 01:59:28,760
Zishe, my son, we're leaving.

1098
01:59:28,880 --> 01:59:31,160
Would you like us to push you over to the window again?

1099
01:59:31,200 --> 01:59:33,480
That would be nice.

1100
01:59:41,280 --> 01:59:44,280
Visiting hours are tomorrow
morning, from 11 o' clock.

1101
01:59:44,280 --> 01:59:45,680
I'm staying.

1102
01:59:45,800 --> 01:59:48,680
- The doctors agreed.
- Benjamin!

1103
01:59:48,760 --> 01:59:52,680
We would like you have you with us as
well sometime. For a whole week now...

1104
01:59:52,760 --> 01:59:57,800
- ...you've come home only to sleep.
- He stays. He can stay.

1105
02:00:00,280 --> 02:00:02,280
Zishe, my son.

1106
02:00:05,880 --> 02:00:07,880
Zishe...

1107
02:00:44,280 --> 02:00:46,880
There's a ringing in my ears.

1108
02:00:47,560 --> 02:00:50,600
Someone must be thinking of me.

1109
02:02:33,400 --> 02:02:35,400
Father...

1110
02:02:38,600 --> 02:02:41,560
Father, Benjamin is flying!

1111
02:02:50,280 --> 02:02:53,040
In spite of his invincible
strenght, Zishe Breitbart...

1112
02:02:53,040 --> 02:02:55,800
...died after eleven
consecutive operations.

1113
02:02:57,280 --> 02:03:02,280
He passed away on January 28, 1933,
two days before Hitler rose to power.

1114
02:03:03,280 --> 02:03:08,280
He lives in leyends and ballads

